This paper is about sequence labeling, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). The paper proposes a new model that combines recurrent neural networks (RNNs) with a latent conditional random field (CRF) to handle complex non-local output constraints. This work is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, but the most likely ones are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). cs.CL is the most likely because the paper deals with NLP tasks, while cs.LG is also relevant because the model uses a neural network and a latent variable model. Other possible sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), as these fields are also related to the topics covered in the paper.
